SWYFTDESKTOP — RESEARCH & DEVELOPMENT NOTES

PROJECT OVERVIEW
SwyftDesktop is a system that connects a mobile phone and a desktop computer into one shared environment.

Phone acts as:
- controller
- input device
- app launcher

Desktop acts as:
- workspace
- app execution environment
- custom interface shell

A communication bridge connects both devices so actions can be sent in real time.

The goal is to create a lightweight desktop experience that works on many devices while keeping the phone usable at all times.

------------------------------------------------------------

CORE IDEA

Instead of separate devices:

Phone = control system
Desktop = visual system
Bridge = communication layer

Actions are sent between devices rather than manually performed on each device.

Example:
Tap button on phone → send command → desktop opens app

