HOW APP LAUNCHING WORKS

Android apps are identified by package names such as:
com.brave.browser

To open an app, Android uses an Intent.

------------------------------------------------------------
CODE: OPENING AN APP

Kotlin example with explanations:

private fun launchApp(packageName: String) {

    // Ask Android system for the launch entry point of the app
    val intent = packageManager.getLaunchIntentForPackage(packageName)

    // If null is returned, the app cannot be opened
    if (intent == null) {

        // Show error message to user
        Toast.makeText(
            this,
            "Cannot launch app: $packageName",
            Toast.LENGTH_LONG
        ).show()

        return
    }

    // Start app in a new task so it runs separately
    intent.addFlags(Intent.FLAG_ACTIVITY_NEW_TASK)

    // Launch the app
    startActivity(intent)
}

------------------------------------------------------------

HOW APP LISTING WORKS

Android does not expose all apps directly.

Only apps that declare themselves as launchable appear in results.

------------------------------------------------------------
CODE: GETTING APPS

private fun getLaunchableApps(): List<AppInfo> {

    // Create intent representing launcher apps
    val intent = Intent(Intent.ACTION_MAIN, null)

    // Filter only apps that appear in app drawer
    intent.addCategory(Intent.CATEGORY_LAUNCHER)

    // Ask system for matching apps
    val apps = packageManager.queryIntentActivities(intent, 0)

    // Convert system app data into simple readable objects
    return apps.map { resolveInfo ->

        AppInfo(
            name = resolveInfo.loadLabel(packageManager).toString(),
            packageName = resolveInfo.activityInfo.packageName
        )
    }
}

------------------------------------------------------------

WHY ONLY SOME APPS SHOW

Apps only appear if:
- they are marked as launcher apps
- they expose a main activity
- system restrictions allow visibility

This is why early testing showed only:
- Settings
- Play Store
- Digital Wellbeing

