ARCHITECTURE CHANGE

System is moving away from:

UI directly doing actions

To:

UI → ACTION → SYSTEM HANDLER → RESULT

This means UI only sends instructions, not logic.

------------------------------------------------------------

CODE: ACTION SYSTEM

sealed class Action {
    data class LaunchApp(val packageName: String) : Action()
}

------------------------------------------------------------

CODE: ACTION HANDLER

fun handleAction(action: Action) {

    when (action) {

        is Action.LaunchApp -> {
            launchApp(action.packageName)
        }
    }
}

------------------------------------------------------------

WHY THIS MATTERS

Without this:
- every button contains logic
- system becomes messy and hard to scale

With this:
- UI is simple
- logic is centralised
- system is expandable into desktop environment

